div.p:
a) "investments means every kind of asset and in particular, though not exclusively, includes:
movable and immovable property and any other property rights such as mortgages, liens or pledges;
shares, stocks and bonds of companies or interests in the property of such companies;
claims dinerarios any benefit or having financial value;
Intellectual Property Rights, including copyrights, patents, trademarks, registered names, industrial designs, trade secrets and know-how, technical processes, key value;
business concessions conferred by law or under contract, including concessions for research, crops, extract or exploit natural resources;

d) "territory means:
with regard to Malaysia, covering the entire territory of the Federation of Malaysia; the territorial sea and its seabed, subsoil and airspace;
with regard to the Eastern Republic of Uruguay, its territory as well as those maritime areas including the seabed and subsoil adjacent to the outer limit of the territorial sea over which Uruguay exercises, in accordance with international law, sovereign rights for the purpose of the exploration and exploitation of natural resources of such areas;
